Our Implementation of the shifter:
We implemented our shifter as a barrel shifter. What this means is that we have four different stages, Shift 1, Shift 2, Shift 4, and Shift 8. When each of these is on we shift by that amount. This allows us to do any set of 15 different shifts by combining turning on of these different stages. We used pass gate logic in our design for the Shift inputs to each of the stages. This allowed us to increase the speed and decrease the dynamic power. Nonetheless, as we will soon show and as was expected it made the fall critical delay much faster than the rise critical delay.

